      "message": "nit: I was wondering what\u0027s the rationale of collecting this time *after* the metrics have been computed, rather than *before*.\n\nIf we read the refs (or the directories, etc) at T0 and finish computation at T1, shouldn\u0027t we expose a collection time of T0, to state that that\u0027s what the metrics are based on?\n\nIn this way, the collection time will always represent the *scheduling* frequency, irrespective of how long it took to process the underlying git data, telling us \"this metrics are based on a read that happened at $collectionTime\"",
